value.0: Which would you care to know about?
They will never accept it, no matter who tries to hand it to 'em. Well, don't say we didn't warn you
Penguins. They decided they like the water SO much, they traded in their wings for flippers. And they were so close...
They. Are on. To us.
Puppets who pull their own strings, or offer them to anybody who wants to make them dance.
Call us deluded? Go look at a Ravnos for a while.

They've just about mortified enough of their own flesh to blast through the wall of delusion from the other side of perception. They're onto something, but who knows if there'll be anything left of them when they get there?
*an explosion of helpless, hysterical giggling*

They aren't animals, no matter what people say. Look under the skin of the corpse, then look under the layer of beast-thought, and what do you find? A secret worse than man, corpse or animal? Yes! Yes!
I can't understand them. Aren't they mad yet? Don't they understand what they've seen? Goddamn. Goddamn. . . .
I want to like your average Brujah, but his skull's just so damned thick that he can't crack it open and get at the good stuff he doesn't even know he's got in there. So forget him
So. That's done, then.

The hierarchy, if it exists at all, defies description. Most of us are usually content to let one another do as they like from night to night. But now and again, in times of great need, we Malkavians demonstrate an uncanny ability to act in unison, even without any apparent leadership - and sometimes even without any apparent communication. As one, we arise from our haunts; as one, we fall on the problem at hand. And when it is a problem no longer, we drift back to their usual games. If the Malkavians indulge in any form of machinations as a clan, we are incomprehensible to outsiders.

We really dont have one but others will tell you that every last vampire of Malkav's blood is irredeemably insane in some form or another. Some attribute this to a curse of the blood, while we actually call it a special blessing, a gift of insight.

We come from all walks of life and for all number of reasons are Embraced. Anyone can be chosen to further a sire's purposes, although most of us prefer Embracing those already close to (or subject to) madness. Most other vampires believe that the Malkavians Embrace their childer on a whim; however, virtually all of us are subtly championing some barely perceptible "purpose," the full extent of which none can properly fathom.

Auspex is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural senses. It is one of the most common and favored Discipline among Cainites due to its versatility and overall usefulness in just about every facet of vampiric existence.Obfuscate is a Discipline that allows vampires to conceal themselves and create some manner of illusions. It is one of the more popular Disciplines practiced by Cainites, and is the source of legends surrounding the ability of vampires to vanish and appear seemingly from nowhere.  Dementation is a Discipline that we are highly known for. It draws on the vampire's own insanity and uses it achieve profound insights or inflict madness upon others.

We by and large take whatever shelter suits us, although more than a few us find aging hospitals and poorly funded asylums to our tastes. Many seem to enjoy the company of desperate mortals, and prefer slums and institutions to more secluded havens. They are just more interesting.
